Phase 2 - UIKit VenuesVC list redesign (`@ios-dev`)

- [x] Keep venues rendered in a vertical list, one venue per row.
- [x] Apply expanded-list style polish (spacing, typography, row card treatment).
- [x] Keep row image/title data mapping behavior unchanged.

Phase 2B - SwiftUI VenuesMigration redesign parity (`@ios-dev`)

- [x] Apply equivalent expanded-list styling in `VenuesMigration` for standard list flow.
- [x] Keep one-row-per-venue vertical list hierarchy and readability parity.
- [x] Keep two-step interaction parity (select first, bottom CTA navigation second).

Phase 3 - Selection details panel (`@ios-dev`)

- [x] Keep bottom details section visible in VenuesVC.
- [x] On selection, display venue name + address in panel.
- [x] Confirm no map is embedded in details panel.
- [x] Add bottom CTA for forward navigation, disabled until venue is selected.

Phase 4 - Preserve contracts and navigation (`@ios-dev`)

- [x] Keep existing function behavior (`addData`, `addLocation`, `navigateBack`, table delegates).
- [x] Keep segue `goto_venues_details` and selected venue propagation unchanged.
- [x] Keep admin/map flow notification behavior unchanged.
- [x] Enforce two-step flow: row tap selects only, bottom CTA triggers navigation.

Phase 5 - Stability and performance (`@ios-dev`)

- [x] Ensure no duplicate subviews are added on repeated appearances.
- [x] Ensure async row image loading remains cell-reuse safe.
- [x] Ensure list remains smooth while scrolling.

Phase 6 - Manual verification handoff (`@user`)

- [ ] Visual verify one-line vertical venues list and polished style.
- [ ] Verify selected venue details/address appears in bottom panel.
- [ ] Verify first tap selects and second tap (bottom CTA) navigates to `VenuesDetailsVC`.
- [ ] Verify no map content appears in bottom details section.
- [ ] Verify map/admin flows still behave as before.
- [ ] Verify UIKit `VenuesVC` and SwiftUI `VenuesMigration` both satisfy redesigned behavior.

